# Archon MCP Tools Guide

## Available MCP Tools (14 total)

### Knowledge Base & RAG
- `rag_get_available_sources` - List knowledge sources
- `rag_search_knowledge_base` - Search with RAG (2-5 keywords)
- `rag_search_code_examples` - Find code snippets
- `rag_list_pages_for_source` - Browse source pages
- `rag_read_full_page` - Get complete page content

### Project Management
- `find_projects` - List/search projects
- `manage_project` - Create/update/delete projects
- `get_project_features` - Get project capabilities

### Task Management
- `find_tasks` - Find tasks by status/project/assignee
- `manage_task` - Create/update/delete tasks
- Task status flow: `todo` → `doing` → `review` → `done`

### Document Management
- `find_documents` - Search project documents
- `manage_document` - Create/update/delete documents

### Version Control
- `find_versions` - List version history
- `manage_version` - Create snapshots/restore versions

## Usage Patterns
```bash
# Research before coding
rag_search_knowledge_base(query="authentication JWT")

# Task-driven development
find_tasks(filter_by="status", filter_value="todo")
manage_task("update", task_id="...", status="doing")

# Project management
find_projects(query="auth")
manage_project("create", title="New Feature")
```

## Best Practices
- Keep search queries short (2-5 keywords)
- Always update task status when working
- Use projects to organize related work
- Research with RAG before implementing features